So I'm beginning with all the basics, starting with importing all the packages that I need

00:08:04.940 --> 00:08:10.380
in my work, setting up my environment, providing API keys and database passwords. I've also

00:08:10.380 --> 00:08:14.579
built some functions for repeatable code that I'm going to use later, and this is where

00:08:14.579 --> 00:08:19.160
I start making a connection to the database, which has all the data about the bike stored.

00:08:19.160 --> 00:08:23.859
So this database is being updated by the RETL process, so I don't need to do the data cleaning

00:08:23.859 --> 00:08:29.100
and exploration. I can directly import this data as a data frame in my Python environment,

00:08:29.100 --> 00:08:32.619
and I can create a testing and training data set and start building my model.

00:08:32.619 --> 00:08:38.659
So for this work, we chose the random forest model, but another iteration of this work

00:08:38.659 --> 00:08:42.179
can be building different kinds of models and comparing their performances. But let's

00:08:42.179 --> 00:08:46.619
take two random forests for this one, and now I've built the model, I need to test it,

00:08:46.619 --> 00:08:51.700
so I create my testing set, and I compare the results with the actual data.

00:08:51.700 --> 00:08:56.900
What I have done here so far is what we do every day as data scientists, right? And maybe

00:08:56.900 --> 00:09:02.520
you all can do it better than I did. But the next challenge for me is to move this model

00:09:02.520 --> 00:09:07.080
